olars. The Handbook to be comprised of five divisions, each telling the story of Jewish philosophy from a distinctive vantage point. Consequently, if one and the same author or work is discussed over several chapters, such overlap should be viewed as presenting a varied and sophisticated perspective on a thinker or text rather than reproducing redundantly the same work or author"-- Provided by publisher.  aImported from: zcat.oclc.org:210/OLUCWorldCat (Do not remove) 0aJewish philosophy. 6aPhilosophie juive.1 aFranks, Paul W.,d1964-4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMelamed, Yitzhak Y.,d1968-4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iOnline versiontOxford handbook of Jewish philosophydNew York, NY, United States of America : Oxford University Press, [2025]z9780190455484  asingle unitbmono  abibliographybbibliography  aindexbindex  a{"@id":"xjpwjvv1vmf1wxs6","modified":"2026-01-08T10:45:06.824+01:00"}2librisxl  5Sax  ab260108||0000|||||000||||||000000eu  5SbShORDER 260108/adlib ABON UNDER INKÖPiBeställdxjn  5Sa{"@id":"bx39x99m8w763sxm","modified":"2026-01-08T10:45:28.252+01:00"}2librisxl02254cam a22003495a sdkrd4m1q6t4bs7xSE-LIBR20260108105105.0260108s2025    nyu|||||||||||000 0|eng|   a2025945896  a9780198960829q(hardback)  z9780198960850  z9780198960836  q(epub)z9780198960850z9780198960836  aSbengcDLCdSeaerda  aeng  apcc1 aKain, Patrick4aut10aKant and the origins of the good will /cPatrick Kain.  a1.  a2512 1aNew York :bOxford University Press,c2025  apages cm  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier  a"The good will and the dignity of humanity are central, but often overlooked or controverted, elements of Kant's moral philosophy. This book investigates the origins and emergence of Kant's moral philosophy and the significance to it of the good will and the dignity of humanity, beginning with some of Kant's early published works, notes, and drafts, and student notes from lectures across various disciplines that he gave over the course of several decades prior to the publication of the Groundwork of the Metaphysics of Morals (1785). The book begins with a historical and philosophical reconstruction of Kant's conception of the divine will, which reflected, influenced, and informed his developing moral philosophy. The book then provides a detailed interpretation of the emergence of Kant's moral philosophy prior to the publication of the Groundwork. This study of the place of the good will and the dignity of humanity in Kant's thought sheds new light on the origins and content of Kant's published works on moral philosophy in the 1780s"--cProvided by publisher.  aImported from: lx2.loc.gov:210/LCDB (Do not remove)  a{"@id":"sdkrd4m1q6t4bs7x","modified":"2026-01-08T10:51:05.777+01:00"}2librisxl  5Sax  ab260108||0000|||||000||||||000000eu  5SbShORDER 260108/adlib ABON UNDER INKÖPiBeställdxjn  5Sa{"@id":"6sz5slht4lqtf9b8","modified":"2026-01-08T10:51:28.545+01:00"}2librisxl01038nac a22002653i 4500001001700000003000800017005001700025008004100042040001900083041000800102110003300110245005200143264001400195336002600209337002800235338002700263650008000290651003300370887008400403950004000487841004900527852004500576866006500621887008600686h38g3sg8f869xstfSE-LIBR20260108104958.0260108i20229999sw |||||||||||000 ||swe|c  aSbsweeierda  aswe2 aEksta hembygdsförening4isb10aEksta hembygdsförening - samling av trycksaker 0c2022-9999  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier 7aHembygdsföreningar0https://id.kb.se/term/sao/Hembygdsf%C3%B6reningar2sao 7aSverigezGotlandzEksta2sao  a{"@id":"h38g3sg8f869xstf","modified":"2026-01-08T10:49:58.678+01:00"}2librisxl kwgaFöreningaruHembygdsföreningar  5Sax  ab260108||0000|||||000||||||000000eu  5SbShVardagstryckl910xvtr2026xcecwra  5Sa2022-zBelagd f