198967019  q(epub)z9780198967033z9780198967019  aSbengcDLCdSeierda  aeng  apcc1 aLangton, Daniel R.4aut10aDarwin in the Jewish imagination :bJews' engagement with evolutionary theory /cDaniel R. Langton.  a1.  a2601 1aNew York :bOxford University Press,c2026  apages cm  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier  a"The development of this project has taken many years and evolved in many unexpected directions as a result of the advice and feedback from many people. The subject is Darwin's Jews, that is, those Jewish thinkers in the late nineteenth- and early twentieth-centuries who have given Darwin a legacy within Jewish history beyond the tragic account of Nazi race theory and eugenics that all too often dominates the discussion of Jews and Darwin. For this reason, as much as any other, it seemed like a worthwhile endeavour. But the identification and selection of the different species of Darwin's Jews has proven to be difficult fieldwork, since there are so many ideological niches and environments for so many varieties of religious and non-religious Jews within the tangled bank of modern Jewish identity. Fortunately, I have not been working alone, and am grateful for the opportunity now to acknowledge the work of others"--cProvided by publisher.  aImported from: lx2.loc.gov:210/LCDB (Do not remove)  a{"@id":"7t06z19v5skkhvl4","modified":"2026-01-08T11:50:52.041+01:00"}2librisxl  5Sax  ab260108||0000|||||000||||||000000eu  5SbShORDER 260108/adlib ABON UNDER INKÖPiBeställdxjn  5Sa{"@id":"j49h8ch2g54g3j81","modified":"2026-01-08T11:51:10.465+01:00"}2librisxl07711ckm a2201681   bx392rv98kng55r7SE-LIBR20260108114601.0cr |||   |||||         260108|        |  |   |     |o   i|zxx| 8 akb-digitization-004836602,2  aS  azxx  9DIGI10aPorträtt föreställande generallöjtnant Bror Cederström  3[original]a1 fotografi  astill imagebsti2rdacontent  adatorbc2rdamed