er kaGenomsiktsbilderuFotografier kaStereobilderuFotografier kwgaIllustrerade verkuBilder kwhaKarikatyrer och skämtteckningaruBilder saCartes de visiteuVisitkortsfotografier saVisitkortsporträttuVisitkortsfotografier kwgaKartonnerade fotografieruVisitkortsfotografier kaVisitkortuVisitkortsfotografier  5Sax  ab260108||0000|||||000||||||000000eu  5SbS  5Sa{"@id":"d05c42nxb5040203","modified":"2026-01-08T11:49:03.562+01:00"}2librisxl03258cam a22005415i bx393bwq8kppb7kmSE-LIBR20260108115349.0260108s2025    nyua|||||b||||001 0|eng|   a2025020344  a9780197809655q(hardcover)  a0197809650q(hardcover)  z9780197809686  z9780197809662  q(PDF)z9780197809686z9780197809662  q(ePub)z9780197809686z9780197809662  a(OCoLC)on1518919331  aSbengcDLCdIG#dOCLCOdYDXdUIUdVXWdSeierda  aeng  apcc 0aBM729.W604a296.082223/eng/202511071 aAckerman, Susan4aut4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aMaturity, marriage, motherhood, mortality :bwomen's life-cycle rituals in ancient Israel /cSusan Ackerman. 1aNew York, NY :bOxford University Press,c[2025]  axv, 391 pagesbillustrationsc25 cm  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier  aIncludes bibliographical references and index.8 aPrologue: Of universals and not -- Introduction: The nature of women's life-cycle rituals -- The birth of a female child -- Women's (and men's) coming of age -- Israelite betrothal rituals -- A young woman's wedding -- Pregnancy and childbirth -- Naming a child -- Nursing and weaning a child -- Menopause -- Ritually marking a woman's death -- Epilogue: Of fragments and (w)holes.  a"Maturity, Marriage, Motherhood, Mortality is a study of women's life-cycle rituals in ancient Israel, beginning with rituals that marked a girl child's birth and then considering a young woman's coming of age and her betrothal and wedding, as well as rituals undertaken by women during pregnancy and during the days and early years after giving birth, before concluding with a discussion of rituals enacted upon a woman's death. Throughout, the book highlights features distinctive to women's life-cycle rituals and especially differences between women's life-cycle rituals and men's, and it puts forward a six-part theoretical model to explain these distinctive features and differences"-- Provided by publisher.  aImported from: zcat.oclc.org:210/OLUCWorldCat (Do not remove) 0aWomen in Judaism. 0aJewish way of life. 0aJudaismxCustoms and practices. 0aLife cycle, HumanxReligious aspectsxJudaism. 6aFemmes dans le judaïsme. 6aJudaïsmexCoutumes et pratiques. 6aVie religieusexJudaïsme.08iOnline versionaAckerman, Susan.tMaturity, marriage, motherhood, mortality.dNew York, NY : Oxford University Press, [2025]z9780197809662  asingle unitbmono  abibliographybbibliography  aindexbindex  a{"@id":"bx393bwq8kppb7km","modified":"2026-01-08T11:53:49.5+01:00"}2librisxl  5Sax  ab260108||0000|||||000||||||000000eu  5SbShORDER 260108/adlib ABON UNDER INKÖPiBeställdxjn  5Sa{"@id":"cz4b4d6h9qqccwdh","modified":"2026-01-08T11:54:15.5+01:00"}2librisxl06856ckm a2201477   vgmtlk1nsfgb4rt8SE-LIBR20260108114928.0cr |||   |||||         260108|        |  |   |     |o   i|zxx| 8 akb-digitization-005023109,1  aS  azxx  9DIGI1 aTesch, Maria,d1850-19364pht0https://libris.kb.se/zw9dmcbh3hnd0rn#it10aPorträtt föreställande Anna Carlander /cMaria Tesch.  3[original]a1 fotografi  astill imagebsti2rdacontent  adatorbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aDigital reproduktionbStockholmcKungliga biblioteketd2026  apublic domain-märke 1.0uhttps://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/14aCarlander, Anna 7aSverige0https://id.kb.se/term/sao/Sverige2sao 7aBilder0https://id.kb.se/term/gmgpc/swe/Bilder2gmgpc/swe 7aPorträtt0https://id.kb.se/term/gmgpc/swe/Portr%C3%A4tt2gmgpc/swe 7aFot