lder kwhaTryckuBilder kwhaNattbilderuBilder kwhaABC-bilderuBilder kwhaAndaktsbilderuBilder kwhaTre bilder i enuBilder kwhaAffischeruBilder kwhaMarina bilderuBilder kwhaIllustrationeruBilder kaElektroniska bilderuBilder kaRitningaruBilder  5Sax  ab260108||0000|||||000||||||000000eu  5SbS  5Sa{"@id":"f16d55j4c6kbd2kz","modified":"2026-01-08T11:49:53.213+01:00"}2librisxl04028cam a22005295i 0lrzr642xmvfd6cpSE-LIBR20260108115616.0260108s2025    nyu||||||b||||001 0|eng|   a2025013433  a9780197682340qpaperback  a0197682340qpaperback  a9780197682333qhardcover  a0197682332qhardcover  z9780197682357  z9780197682371  z9780197682364  qelectronic bookz9780197682357z9780197682371z9780197682364  qelectronic bookz9780197682357z9780197682371z9780197682364  qelectronic bookz9780197682357z9780197682371z9780197682364  a(OCoLC)on1506820052  aSbengcDLCdOCLCOdIG#dYDXdBDXdYDXdVXWdSeierda  aeng  apcc 0aB1663.S74400a146/.42223/eng/2025041810aSusan Stebbing :banalysis, common sense, and public philosophy /cedited by Annalisa Coliva and Louis Doulas. 1aNew York, NY :bOxford University Press,c[2025]  axx, 270 pagesc24 cm.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  aunmediatedbn2rdamedia  avolumebnc2rdacarrier1 aOxford new histories of philosophy series  aIncludes bibliographical references and index.8 aSusan Stebbing: Analysis, common sense, and public philosophy / Annalisa Coliva and Louis Doulas -- The significance of Susan Stebbing's work on analysis / Annalisa Coliva -- Stebbing on clarity / Eric Schliesser -- Susan Stebbing's anti-idealist philosphy of physics: Her rebuttal of Eddington's argument from intrinsic nature / Frederique Janssen-Lauret -- Making sense of Stebbing and Moore on common sense / Louis Doulas -- Susan Stebbing's critique of popular science: Guiding or gatekeeping? / Karl Egerton -- Stebbing's pelicans: Public philosophy in Philosophy and the physicists and thinking to some purpose / Peter West -- Susan Stebbing and some poorly explored venues of analytic philosophy / Nikolay Milkov -- Susan Stebbing and the politics of symbolic logic / David E. Dunning -- Susan Stebbing: Philosophy, pragmatics, and critical discourse analysis / Siobhan Chapman -- Stebbing on linguistic convention: Understanding, definition, and verbal disputes / Bryan Pickel -- Stebbing, translations, and verbal disputes / Teresa Kouri Kissel.  a"This volume is the first to be dedicated exclusively to the philosophy of Susan Stebbing (1885-1943)-a pivotal figure in early analytic philosophy who has, until recently, been unjustly neglected. The eleven historical essays that comprise the volume explore (many for the first time) various elements of Stebbing's prolific output: the significance of her work on metaphysical analysis, her contributions to public philosophy, including her work in the philosophy of physics, critical thinking, ethics, and counterpropaganda efforts, as well as her work in philosophical logic and the philosophy of language. The volume endeavors to reinstate Stebbing's place in the analytic tradition by examining her ideas in context and elucidating their significance, many of which are still relevant to present day philosophy"-- Provided by publisher.  aImported from: zcat.oclc.org:210/OLUCWorldCat (Do not remove)10aStebbing, L. Susanq(Lizzie Susan),d1885-19431 aColiva, Annalisa,d1973-4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDoulas, Louis4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt 0aOxford new histories of philosophy  asingle unitbmono  aindexbindex  a{"@id":"0lrzr642xmvfd6cp","modified":"2026-01-08T11:56:16.468+01:00"}2librisxl  5Sax  ab260108||0000|||||000||||||000000eu  5SbShORDER 260108/adlib ABON UNDER INKÖPiBeställdxjn  5Sa{"@id":"7t060g8g5dz2c632","modified":"2026-01-08T11:56:35.988+01:00"}2librisxl04593nkm a22011177i xjpwnmk7vwkwnf08SE-LIBR20260108114940